This paper deals with regular path queries, which are a fundamental component of graph query languages. The paper focuses on the evaluation problem for RPQs under trail semantics, which is a topic that falls under the database systems (cs.DB) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The trichotomy result and the study of the tractable class, its expressivity, and closure properties are related to formal languages and automata theory, which are topics covered by the logic in computer science (cs.LO) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the decision and enumeration problems, which are relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
